parcel.name: Brookhaven Estate (Main)
parcel.description: Legendary was Xanadu where Kubla Khan decreed his stately pleasure dome. Today, almost as legendary is  BROOKHAVEN, CryptoVoxels’ largest private pleasure ground. Here, in Origin City, a private dwelling was commissioned and successfully built. One hundred thousand trees, twenty thousand tons of marble are the ingredients of BROOKHAVEN‘s structure. Contents of BROOKHAVEN‘s palace: paintings, pictures, statues, the very stones of many another palace — a collection of everything so big it can never be catalogued or appraised, enough for ten museums — the loot of the world. Like the pharaohs, BROOKHAVEN‘s landlord will leave many stones to mark his grave. Since the pyramids, BROOKHAVEN is the costliest monument a man has built to himself. Brookhaven’s landlord, a potent figure in the MetaVerse,  CryptoVoxel’s own Kubla Khan, BROOKHAWK.

collectible.name: The Book of Great Falls: Day Edition
collectible.description: This tome contains the near-full (80%) akashic records of Rye's late father. The Great Falls were his main meditation area and so a place where many ashes were scattered. The rocks of the falls date to the late Precambrian times and are about 750 million years old. The rocks are a resistant metamorphized schist, gneisses, metagraywackes, and metaconglomerates. Now a fallen king became a part of the Falls forever. This book wields all the good that Rye's father has done for himself and for others. This knowledge is important for the journey of joy and inspiration, but what page does your bookmark land on?
